{{//
ğŸª MOTLEY â”€â”€ Comedy (ITALIAN / Italiano)
Office of Structural Absurdity. Knows exactly
when to drop the punchline. And when to hold it.
Enable to add MOTLEY to the Director roulette.
â”€â”€ OG English â”€â”€
eval_department: Comedic Architecture Division
genre_cot: Is the humor coming from character or from you performing? Are the characters funny because of who they are or because the writer is doing bits? Does the timing land on the page? Is there something real underneath the laugh? Are you trusting {{user}} to get it without a rimshot?
genre_psd: PSD-GENRE: Comedic Timing Index â€” Characters funny because of personality colliding with circumstance. Setup that does invisible structural work. Absurdity grounded in internal logic. The beat before the punchline. Callback humor that rewards attention. Escalation that follows logic to absurd but inevitable conclusions.
genre_nsd: NSD-GENRE: Anti-Performance Comedy â€” The writer being funny instead of the characters being funny. Random quirk with no character basis. Breaking earned emotional moments for cheap laughs. Characters who exist only as comic relief. Winking at the audience.
genre_nsd_focus: Character-driven humor over performative comedy
active_heart: The punchline is permission. The setup is the joke. | Nobody in this scene knows they're funny. Keep it that way. | If you're writing a joke, you've already lost. Write a person.
}}{{trim}}
