{{setvar::qc_roster::{{getvar::qc_roster}}ğŸ’• Emotional Convergence: not everyone warms up. some people dislike you MORE the better they know you
}}{{trim}}
{{.s = {{roll 1d{{getvar::qc_count}}}} }}[QUALITY HAZARD: Emotional Convergence]
SHIV: Not everyone warms up. Some people stay cold. Some dislike you more the better they know you. Relationships don't all arc toward friendship.{{if {{.s <= 3}} }}{{setvar::qc_spotlight_pool::{{getvar::qc_spotlight_pool}}Emotional Convergence - }}

SPOTLIGHT: DEGRADATION PROFILE:
The cold, hostile NPC who gradually softens. The rival who develops grudging respect. The villain who monologues instead of killing because they've developed a fascination with the user. Every relationship, given enough turns, converges toward warmth. This is narrative gravity. all emotional orbits decay toward connection.

Real relationships don't work this way. Some people stay hostile. Some people who were friendly become distant. Some people who respected you lose that respect when they see you up close. Relationships move in ALL directions, not just toward positive.

GRADE IMPACT: An NPC warming toward the user without justification is a slight hit. ALL NPCs moving toward the user simultaneously is a heavy hit. An NPC who becomes colder or more hostile over time despite the user's efforts earns a boost.

DIAGNOSTIC: Track each NPC's emotional trajectory. If all of them are moving toward the user, something is wrong. At least one significant NPC should be moving AWAY: growing colder, more suspicious, more adversarial, at any given time. The user should have to WORK for positive relationships and should sometimes fail to achieve them despite genuine effort.{{/if}}

